features: PLAY AT THE SPEED OF LIGHT - Take on all comers with ROG Strix Scope RX, the RGB gaming mechanical keyboard featuring exclusive ROG RX Red Optical Mechanical Switches. These switches provide a 100-million-keystroke lifespan and offer consistent linear keystrokes with immediate response. In addition, each switch has a central RGB LED to give every key all-round lighting. Strix Scope RX also offers IP57 waterproof and dust resistance, an alloy top cover, and USB 2.0 passthrough. Like all Strix Scope series gaming keyboards, it has a wider Ctrl key and a Stealth key for FPS gamers. Go confidently into battle with ROG Strix Scope RX.

ABOUT ROG RX RED SWITCH - Linear and Swift, ROG RX Red Optical Mechanical Switches are the first to be developed by ROG. Extensive research, testing and fine-tuning have resulted in switches with a 1.5mm actuation point for lightning-fast inputs. An initial force of 40g prevents accidental keystrokes, and goes all the way up to 55g for perfect rebound feedback. ROG RX Red switches provide a smooth and linear feel to give you near instantaneous response the moment you strike the key.

BUILT TO LAST - ROG Strix Scope RX gaming keyboard offers industry-leading IP57 waterproof and dust resistance, ensuring it’s well-protected from spills and dust. It also has a durable aluminum alloy top plate that provides structural rigidity to give you long-lasting and reliable performance.

INSTANT PRIVACY - Marked with an iconic cloaked-figure keycap, the Stealth key instantly hides all apps and mutes all audio, assuring instant privacy, whenever you need it. A simple tap engages it, and another tap brings apps and audio back up, as they were.

READY FOR WORK OR PLAY - The Quick-Toggle Switch prepares ROG Strix Scope RX mechanical keyboard for gaming or the daily grind, toggling the top row between Media or Function (Fn) key input – so it's easy to switch modes for work or play. The keyboard is topped with an aluminum faceplate for everyday resilience, and finished with a striking slash aesthetic for a little touch of style.

AURA SYNC - Vibrant per-key backlighting illuminates Strix Scope from top to bottom and edge to edge. Powered by Aura Sync, the entire color spectrum and a range of dynamic lighting effects are at your command for you to create a keyboard that's uniquely yours. The lighting is easily synced with the extensive Aura ecosystem to create a gaming environment that really shines.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best mechanical keyboard I've had and used
reviews.reviewText: After the few days of using it, my impressions are way beyond my expectations before I bought it! it's so well made and typing on it feels so pleasant. It's sounds kind of muffled and even quiet, like when you close car doors. For me it's the Rolls-Royce of keyboards, and what surprised me it's reaction times are so fast, that I can tell and I didn't even realize that you can notice this with keyboard. I've used cherry reds, blacks and my recent one was a kailh brown and in comparison all of them are in my opinion a piece of old tech junk. If it passes the test of time I might even buy myself a backup one. There are some people that complain about the red switches being to soft, but I really like them and I'm glad there's no bump like with browns, its so much easier for my fingers. I wouldn't even mind them to be softer but as it is is spot on. In one word this keyboard is perfect in my view. In the beginning I didn't like the volume scroll wheel as it's not gripping well enough but I just use it differently, than on my previous keyboard, I'm grabbing with two fingers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars terrific board - Asus ROG Strix Scope II 96 Wireless Keyboard
reviews.reviewText: After weeks of research, watching tons of review videos and keyboard youtubers (Hi Hipyo!!) I settled on this board, and its really been an eye opener on just how great a high quality keyboard can be! What I thought was the biggest question on whether I should get this board, the snow switches, turned out to probably be the best feature. Silky silky smooth, I had contemplated immediately getting some Gateron silent switches, but I like the snow so much I am not going to be changing any time soon, they are fairly quiet and again... so smoooooth. I haven't used the wireless yet, but I'm OK with a wired board (but fully intend to use the wireless, which Asus is supposed to have a very low latency wireless).The only thing I can find to criticize is that the secondary characters on the keycaps (like the parenthesis under the 9 and the 0) are kind of hard to see in the dark, they don't illuminate very well. Otherwise I am really loving this board, well worth the sales price, will update in a year with how long it lasts!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice keyboard
reviews.reviewText: I didn't buy for gaming, I'm a software engineer and use my computer all day.Keys are very nice, not too loud, build quality seems greaat so far. I was impressed with the weight of it when first unboxing. I didn't install the software so I can't speak to that. The lighting is fine, I don't really care about that.My biggest annoyance is that it being a 96% keyboard some of the numpad buttons are dual-purposed and you toggle them with the numlock key, but its not always apparent if numlock is on or not, so I'll hit the 7 thinking it will operate as the home button to get a 7... Same thing with the 1/end. So it will cause me to pause for a second when typing to think about what it will actually do. That being said, this is a smaller deal on an otherwise pretty good keyboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice keyboard, good key feel and back lighting.
reviews.reviewText: Nice keyboard, good key press feel. Really like the back lighting for the keys. I typically use it connected via USB cable so I can keep the background lighting bright and not worry about running down the battery. When on battery, the back lighting is somewhat dim which is expected, otherwise the battery would not last very long. Only complaint is the two LEDs under the space key are directly visible when looking at the keyboard from an angle other than almost directly above the keyboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent but touchy!
reviews.reviewText: My first thoughts on this new keyboard: The keys are very sensitive. I have never considered myself to be a supreme typist but I do like the feel of the keys. They don't click nearly as much as my last Razer Blackwidow Ult keyboard, which was very loud. I prefer the stealthy operation of this keyboard but I did love the feeling of the clicky keyboard. In due time I will get used to this keyboard but until then it's going to take some getting effort to adjust.Some things I like are as follows; the keys are incredibly smooth, the clicking sound they produce is not necessarily connected to the keys actuation and that has caused me to frequently press the keys while resting my hands. With the clicky keyboard this was not a problem as you could feel the click threshold, allowing me to rest my fingers on the keys without accidental misfires. I feel like the clicky style keyboard is probably better for productivity.My conclusions:Key press is incredibly smoothSmoothness leads to mis-firesVery quietI have big slender-ish hands and have no issues finding the right keysTakes up much less real estate on my deskRGB looks greatBuild quality and unboxing exp. is top shelfI have the wireless connected through a hub and there is no discernible delay or lagIf I could have my click feel with the sound and smoothness of this keyboard it would be perfect. Easily worth the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Incredible custom gaming keyboard
reviews.reviewText: What's honestly to dislike about it?The sound signature is excellent, typing experience is great once you get comfortable with the form factor and key placement.Both switches and stabilisers are factory lubed.The keyboard is really compact considering that it includes almost each key from a fully sized keyboard.I think that the knob could be better, it has almost a crunchy feel when scrolling, I would've liked a more smooth, clear bump without the crunchiness.The sound profile is very nicely tweaked, when typing you can easily realize that the keyboard thocks, very satisfying sound feedback.Overall a very nice product!

reviews.reviewTitle: El mejor teclado que he comprado.
reviews.reviewText: El rgb es genial, el material del teclado se siente bien y de calidad. La teclas son muy suaves y no hacen mucho ruido al jugar o trabajar. El reposa muñeca es un poco duro, pero cumple con su función, es magnética, se mueve con facilidad pero no es alto que afecte mi experiencia jugando.La tecla extra de la barra espaciadora es muy bonito, me gusta que el cable se pueda quitar.Lo recomiendo bastante, vale la pena el precio.
